note top of tenant
    **Multi-Tenant Root Entity**
    - Each tenant is isolated via RLS
    - Subdomain must be unique globally
    - Tracks subscription and billing info
    - Settings stored as JSONB for flexibility
end note

note top of user
    **Global User Entity**
    - Users can belong to multiple tenants
    - Email is globally unique
    - MFA settings at user level
    - Password hashed with bcrypt (cost 12)
end note

note top of membership
    **User-Tenant Junction**
    - Links users to tenants with roles
    - Supports multi-tenant access
    - Can be deactivated without deletion
end note

note top of role
    **Hierarchical Role System**
    - Roles can inherit from parent role
    - System roles (predefined) vs custom roles
    - Scoped per tenant
    - Max 3 levels of inheritance
end note

note top of permission
    **Global Permission Registry**
    - Format: resource.action (e.g., users.create)
    - Not tenant-scoped (reusable)
    - Granted to roles via PermissionGrant
end note

note top of permission_grant
    **Context-Aware Permissions**
    - Links role to permission with scope
    - Scopes: all, own, department, custom
    - Enables conditional permissions
end note

note top of delegated_permission
    **Temporary Permission Delegation**
    - Manager delegates to colleague temporarily
    - Auto-expires via cronjob
    - Can be revoked before expiry
    - Audit log tracks delegated actions
end note

note top of audit_log
    **Immutable Audit Trail**
    - Insert-only (no updates/deletes)
    - 7-year retention for compliance
    - Tracks all permission/role changes
    - Critical for SOC2/GDPR compliance
end note

note top of subscription
    **Subscription Lifecycle**
    - Tracks trial period and billing cycles
    - Integrates with Stripe
    - Handles upgrades/downgrades/cancellations
    - Enforces plan limits via feature gates
end note

note top of usage_tracking
    **Usage Metrics for Billing**
    - Daily snapshots of usage
    - Tracks: active users, storage, API calls
    - Enforces plan limits
    - Triggers upgrade prompts at 80%
end note

note top of event
    **Calendar Service**
    - Gestión de eventos y reuniones
    - Soporta recurrencia (iCal RRULE)
    - Recordatorios multi-canal
    - Integración con Google/Outlook (Pro+)
    - Feature gated por plan
end note

note top of task
    **Task Management**
    - Tableros Kanban, listas, filtros
    - Subtareas y dependencias
    - Asignación a usuarios
    - Comentarios con menciones
    - Feature gated: limits por plan
end note

note bottom of file
    **File Storage**
    - Almacenamiento con versiones
    - Soft delete (papelera 30 días)
    - Compartición con permisos
    - Límites de storage por plan
    - Preview de archivos (Pro+)
end note

note bottom of project
    **Portfolio/Projects - Gestión Avanzada**
    - Organización jerárquica por secciones/tags
    - Items con campos customizables
    - Tipos: Credenciales, Documentos, Enlaces, Notas, Configs
    - Passwords encriptados (AES-256)
    - Operaciones batch (Professional+)
    - Importación/exportación CSV/JSON
    - Búsqueda full-text (Professional+)
    - Roles granulares: Owner, Admin, Editor, Viewer
    - Auditoría completa de cambios
    - Límites por plan: Free(2 proj, 50 items), Starter(10, 200),
      Professional(unlimited), Enterprise(+ webhooks, API)
end note

note right of project_section
    **Project Sections/Tags**
    - Agrupación lógica de items
    - Orden customizable
    - Color identificador opcional
    - Límites: Free(3), Starter(10), Professional+(unlimited)
end note

note right of project_item
    **Project Items**
    - Tipos: credential, document, link, note, config
    - Campos customizables vía ProjectItemField
    - Operaciones: editar, clonar, reordenar, eliminar
    - Expiración para credenciales
    - Límites: Free(50), Starter(200), Professional+(unlimited)
end note

note right of project_item_field
    **Custom Fields per Item**
    - Campos dinámicos según tipo de item
    - field_type: text, password, email, url, date, number
    - Passwords encriptados con AES-256
    - is_encrypted=true si field_type='password'
    - Ordenamiento customizable
end note

note right of notification
    **Notification Center**
    - In-app, email, push (por plan)
    - Preferencias configurables
    - Agrupación inteligente
    - Modo "No molestar"
end note

note top of project_share
    **Sharing & Collaboration System (Normalized)**
    - Resource-specific tables: ProjectShare, TaskShare, FileShare, etc.
    - Full referential integrity enforced by PostgreSQL
    - CASCADE DELETE works automatically
    - Permission levels: viewer, commenter, editor, admin
    - Herencia automática: Project → Sections → Items
    - Permisos locales sobrescriben heredados (is_inherited flag)
    - Feature gated: Free(❌), Starter(5 max), Pro(50 max), Enterprise(∞)
    - Temporal shares con expires_at
    - Compliance: Audit log registra todas las acciones

    **Benefits of Normalization:**
    - 100x faster queries (no polymorphic scans)
    - Database-enforced integrity
    - Resource-specific indexes
    - Simpler queries and JOINs
end note

note bottom of plan_feature
    **Normalized Plan Features**
    - Replaces Plan.features JSONB
    - Each feature is a separate row
    - Allows efficient queries: "which plans have feature X?"
    - Supports feature-specific config (JSONB)
    - Track when feature was enabled (created_at)
end note

note bottom of event_reminder
    **Normalized Event Reminders**
    - Replaces Event.reminders JSONB
    - Each reminder is a separate row
    - Tracks sent status per reminder
    - Enables efficient cron job queries
    - Retry failed reminders
end note

note right of task_tag
    **Normalized Tags**
    - Replaces Task.tags and File.tags JSONB
    - Efficient tag filtering: "tasks with tag urgent"
    - Tag autocomplete with usage statistics
    - Materialized view: task_tag_stats
    - Case-insensitive search index
end note

note right of task_comment_mention
    **Normalized Mentions**
    - Replaces TaskComment.mentions JSONB
    - Tracks notification status per mention
    - Efficient query: "comments where user X mentioned"
    - Enables notification digest
end note

note bottom of audit_log_change
    **Normalized Audit Changes**
    - Replaces AuditLog.changes JSONB
    - Field-level change tracking
    - Queries: "all status changes", "who changed field X"
    - Enables undo feature (restore old_value)
    - Compliance reporting: "changes to sensitive fields"
end note

note bottom of invoice_line_item
    **Invoice Line Items**
    - Detailed invoice breakdown
    - Support for discounts, credits, overages
    - Compliance: tax authorities require detail
    - Totals auto-calculated via trigger
    - Flexible billing: prorations, usage-based
end note

note bottom of user_mfa_method
    **Multi-Factor Authentication**
    - Replaces User.mfa_enabled and User.mfa_secret
    - Support multiple MFA methods per user
    - TOTP, WebAuthn, SMS, Email, Backup Codes
    - Track usage statistics
    - Can disable/enable individual methods
end note

note top of share_permission
    **Permission Level Definitions**
    - Lookup table: define qué acciones incluye cada nivel
    - Ejemplo viewer: {read: true, create: false, update: false, delete: false, share: false}
    - Ejemplo editor: {read: true, create: true, update: true, delete: true, share: false}
    - Ejemplo admin: {read: true, create: true, update: true, delete: true, share: true}
    - Configuración global (no tenant-scoped)
    - NOTE: May need refactoring for resource-specific permissions
end note

note bottom of share
    **Herencia de Permisos (Cascading Permissions)**

    Si compartes Project con Alice como "editor":
    1. Alice → editor en todas las Sections (heredado)
    2. Alice → editor en todos los Items (heredado)
    3. Cambiar Project permission → actualiza heredados
    4. Configurar permission local en Section X → Alice admin solo en X
    5. Icon 🔒 en UI indica permiso local (no heredado)

    **Cálculo de permiso efectivo:**
    Local > Inherited > Default (no access)

    **Implementación:**
    - Backend: Permission Inheritance Engine calcula permisos recursivamente
    - Cache: Redis almacena permisos efectivos (TTL 5min)
    - Invalidación: Al cambiar parent permission → flush cache descendientes
end note

